3. Overview of Spring Framework’s Support for REST API Development

Spring Framework is a popular Java framework for building web applications, including
RESTful APIs. Spring provides several modules to make REST API development easy and efficient.

Key Spring Modules for REST:

Spring Web MVC:
Handles HTTP requests and responses, mapping URLs to Java methods.

Spring Boot:
Simplifies setup and configuration, allowing you to create REST APIs quickly with minimal boilerplate.

Spring Data:
Integrates with databases, making it easy to manage resources.

How Spring Supports REST:

(i)  Annotation-Based Configuration:
Use annotations like @RestController, @RequestMapping, @GetMapping, @PostMapping, etc., to
define REST endpoints.

(ii)  Automatic JSON/XML Serialization:
Spring automatically converts Java objects to JSON or XML for API responses.

(iii) Exception Handling:
Use @ExceptionHandler or @ControllerAdvice to handle errors gracefully.

(iv) Validation:
Use @Valid and validation annotations to ensure data integrity.